<br>
A question to a guild(since they are a large group of similarly thinking people) would be, &quot;What place does your guild have with such and such town/city/culture.&quot;<br>
<br>
Lets make up a fictional guild.<br>
<br>
Have a good aligned guild created on the beliefs of Tunare. What function do they have in say Kelethin? Are they guardians of the city like the Emerald Warriors? Do they explore the lands to combat their enemies like the Faydark Champions? Are they more freelance and not actaully connected to the city? What do they do as part of the Wood Elf culture? What role do they have? If it is a family oriented guild, then who is related to who and how? Or are they more of a club calling each other family in some why like some in real life clubs the members call each other brothers.<br>
<br>
I know most guilds are racially mixed, but there must be quite a majority of one race or another. For example, most evil aligned guilds have a Teir'dal structure to them (Dark elves are just the most numerous evil race), and use the Dark Elf langauge(while good aligned use elvish, the most numerous good aligned race). So they would probably be of the dark elf culture. This doesn't mean they have to use drow (or heaven forbid a good aligned guild speaking elvish hehe, well if they do... good for ya, thats a tough language to learn, at least for me)<br>
<br>
We spend far too much time focusing on only a part of the cultures, that being just alignment. There are other things too. For example when I played a rogue, I had some warriors look down on me(RPwise, they loved having my DPS in the group OOC) because my way of fighting was different then theirs. I would like to see more of this kind of RP alongside the alignment. I see people use the LFG and in the comments it says &quot;Good only pls&quot;. Sorry thats not really RPing, but lets say a paladin is LFG. A necromancer asks him to join a group and the paladin responds, &quot;You follow the dark arts, I will not aid you.&quot; Now thats a bit better then &quot;No evils pls&quot; Gives more interaction. If your guild restricts what alignments you can group with, they are doing it to entice their members to RP (hopefully, there's a problem if it isn't). Now I am not saying warriors and rogues should not group. But say I am a warrior and that rogue takes agro and has to evade, my warrior is going to chuckle and ridicule the rogue. Then the rogue may smirk and BS the mob doing alot more damage then the warrior. Then again the warrior would probably come up with an excuse and say it was a lucky shot. This is just a personal example, there are other things you can do. Just remember its not all good and evil (lets not forget Law and Chaos). They took out those restrictions to let us use our imaginations, lets do that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=freelancewizard>FreelanceWizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Musician of<br>
