<br>
Oh, yes, differing philosophies make for excellent RP. One thing that would go a long way in this regard, IMHO, would be coming up with some metaphysical explanations for magic (especially bardic magic, which currently has basically none). Not a lot of lore (practically none that I've seen) discusses the metaphysical underpinnings of magic; beyond that clerical and necromantic magics come from the gods, most of the Art remains in the D&amp;D vein of &quot;do X and cause Y.&quot; Some essays on metaphysics, while not canon and maybe not all in agreement with each other, would give a lot of interesting ideas to some.<br>
<br>
Of course, maybe I'm the only one interested in metaphysics, and maybe I'm the only one that considers them part of the culture of spellcasters. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.realitywerks.com/hosted-images/elludensig.png" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
